</head>
<body><!--main section for content being displayed-->
    <div class="container"><!---->
        <h1>Todo List: </h1><!--Main title displayed on page-->
        <ul class="todoItems"><!--this holds an unorded list with a class of todoItems-->
        <% for(let i=0; i < items.length; i++) {%><!--Use EJS to start a for loop-->
            <li class="item"><!--Creates a list item with the class of item-->
                <% if(items[i].completed === true) {%><!--Use EJS to check if certain item has a completed property of true-->
                    <span class='completed'><%= items[i].thing %></span><!--Use EJS to insert the item in the span that was created with the class of completed-->
                <% }else{ %><!--the else part of the item-->
                    <span><%= items[i].thing %></span><!--if the item does not have a completed property, then use ejs to put a span with no class with the current item in the list-->
                <% } %><!--use the ejs to end the conditional statement--> 
                <span class='fa fa-trash'></span><!--an empty span with a class of fa fa-trash its font awesome icons to display a trash can-->
            </li><!--we close the list item like normal-->
        <% } %><!--EJS to close the for loop-->
        </ul><!--the closing tag for our unordered list-->

        <h2>Left to do: <%= left %></h2><!--h2 tag using EJS to display the variable left which shows how many tasks are left to complete-->

        <h2>Add A Todo:</h2><!--h2 tag to display add a todo:-->

        <form action="/addTodo" method="POST"><!--creates a form with a POST method that goes to the  /addTodo route when submitted-->
            <input type="text" placeholder="Thing To Do" name="todoItem"><!--the input tag creates a field/box that we can interact with, it accepts text with the type, the placeholder is was the box says before we type in it,  and the name is what this input is going to be called so we can reference it later-->
            <input type="submit"><!--creates a button with the type of submit so we can send the information that the form holds-->
        </form><!--closing the form tag-->
    </div>
    

    <script src='js/main.js'></script><!--linking to the main.js file that is in the js folder which we can find in the public folder-->
</body><!--close out the body tag-->
</html><!--close out the html tag-->
